	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-29T04:34:12">Camellia Plc is a United Kingdom-based holding company. The Company and its subsidiaries are engaged in the agriculture and horticulture, engineering, food storage and distribution, private banking and financial services, and the holding of property and investments. The Company operates through five segments: Agriculture and horticulture, Engineering, Food storage and distribution, Banking and financial services, and Other operations. The Agriculture and horticulture segment is engaged in the production of tea, edible nuts, citrus, rubber, fruits, other horticultural produce and general farming. The Engineering segment is engaged in metal finishing, precision engineering and heat treatment. The Company's subsidiaries include Amgoorie India Limited, C.C. Lawrie Comercio e Participacoes Ltda., Eastern Produce Cape (Pty) Limited, Eastern Produce Kenya Limited, Eastern Produce Malawi Limited, Eastern Produce South Africa (Pty) Limited and Atfin GmbH, among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-08-27T23:45:51">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Camellia Plc revenues increased 1% to L102.5M. Net loss increased 34% to L8M. Revenues reflect Agriculture and Horticulture segment increase of 6% to L65M, Banking/Interest/Investments segment increase of 10% to L6.7M, Food Storage and Distribution segment increase of 2% to L15.2M. Higher net loss reflects Agriculture and Horticulture segment loss increase from L1.3M to L3.6M.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
